description: These quinoa snack bars are a nutritious treat packed with seeds and delicious vanilla.
keywords: Snack,Pescatarian,Halal,Seafood free,Low salt,Wheat free,Vegetarian,Egg free,Dairy free
name: Crunchy Quinoa Snack Bars Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Pre-heat the oven to 160°C/140°C fan-forced and line a square baking tray with parchment paper.
Add the dates to a food processor and pulse to form a thick dough 1-2 minutes. Place in a large bowl.
Add the quinoa, pecans, seeds, tahini and vanilla to the dates and mix very well with a metal spoon to form a stiff dough.
Add the dough to the baking tray and press into the tin to form an even layer, as tightly packed as possible. Bake for 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from the oven and allow to cool for 1 hour, then place in the fridge for 1 hour to firm up further. Remove from the fridge and slice into 12 rectangular bars.
